HEADWORD: Cultrivorous
<hw>Cul*triv"o*rous</hw> <pr>(k?l-tr?b"?-r?s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>culter</ets>, <ets>cultri</ets>, knife + <ets>vorare</ets>
to devour.]</ety> <def>Devouring knives; swallowing, or pretending to
swallow, knives; -- applied to persons who have swallowed, or have
seemed to swallow, knives with impunity.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Culturable</ent>⟦br⟧
